
Olivia and Ava White (born June 24, 2005) began acting when they were only 10 weeks old, guest starring on Veronica Mars and Ghost Whisperer. At the age of 6 months old, they landed the recurring role of Claire Kiriakis on the NBC soap Days of Our Lives. 

The girls simultaneously held the recurring role of Carrie Greco in the ABC primetime show What About Brian during its second and final season while also being on ''Days of our Lives''. They appeared in a total of 11 episodes out of the total of 19 second season episodes on What About Brian. After only 9 months of being on Days of Our Lives, the two were put on contract with the show, keeping them on for at least another two years. As of November 192007, the girls have appeared in 100 episodes of Days of Our Lives. 

Olivia and Ava hold the distinction of being the youngest children ever to be put on contract onsoap opera.;IMDB biography of Ava and Olivia [http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2265158/bio];;TV.com biography of Ava and Olivia.;The girls have two other older siblings; a sister, Alexis, who is six years older and a brother, Jack, who is four years older.

